What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Industrial Margarine Market?



Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Industrial Margarine Market

Industrial margarine market size is expected to grow at a compound annual rate of 4.50% in the forecast period 2021 to 2028. The rise in the product acceptance and usage is the factor responsible for the growth of industrial margarine market in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

Margarine is a type of a non-dairy product made from animal fat and vegetable. Industrial margarine is also used as a substitute for butter used for baking, toppings, spreads and other cooking purposes.

The major growing factor towards industrial margarine market is the rise in consumption of margarine and changing tastes and preferences of consumers. Furthermore, the high growth of the food industry and low price of margarine are also expected to heighten the overall demand for industrial margarine market over the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Moreover, the high adoption of margarine products and rapid change in the lifestyle of the people may leads to increase in high blood pressure problems are also expected to serve as foremost drivers for the industrial margarine market at a global level. In addition, the rise in the westernization of food dishes and increase in the health-conscious customers is also lifting the growth of the industrial margarine market.

However, the compliance with international quality standards and strict regulations are projected to act as a restraint towards the growth of industrial margarine market, whereas the rise in the health awareness and obesity concerns can challenge the growth of the industrial margarine market.

Moreover, the rise in the convenience food industry, high growth of the confectionery and bakery market in emerging economies such as India and China and the rapid shift in focus toward convenient and instantly processed food are expected to further generate new opportunities for the industrial margarine market in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

